$interpreted: Kittyeyes:  Roger, didn't you promise that we would live a happy life together? Please, return to the real you!
Roger: ......
Roger: I-I'm back...
Kittyeyes: Thank goodness. We can't be apart again...
Kittyeyes: Like you promised, we will always be together, happily ever after...
Roger: ...What are you talking about? You're my sister. We have always been together, haven't we?
Roger: Not only did we survive Atlas together, we grew up in Elana Village too...
Kittyeyes: Elana Village? No, that's your younger sister Lina...
Roger: Lina!? Who is Lina? My blood-related sister has always been you, Kittyeyes, and only you, right?
Kittyeyes: .....
Roger: ... Kittyeyes, I'm feeling a bit exhausted. Let me get some shut-eye, ok?
Kittyeyes: Uh-huh, sure. Take your time and rest up.
Kittyeyes: I'll take care of the rest...
Kittyeyes: He's safe, there's nothing more I can ask for. Everything else is not important...
Aosta: Who would have thought that under the influence of the void energy, he'd be able to suppress the takeover consciously?
Aosta: Even though his memory is now in utter chaos, he's still a valuable experimental material.
Aosta: Should benefit my research in one way or another.
Kittyeyes: Aosta? Why are you here...
Kittyeyes: By the way, where's Koll?
Aosta: Time is of the essence when studying experimental materials. Stop wasting my time!
Kittyeyes: I-I will not allow you to come near Roger...
Aosta: Playtime's over, begone!
Aosta: Still trying to save the day?
Kittyeyes: I've always caused trouble for Koll and brother Roger. They are in their current situation because of me.
Kittyeyes: I can't always be causing trouble. Now it's my turn to protect everybody!
Roger: You freak, again; What are you trying to do to my sister?
Aosta: Tsk...forget it.
Kittyeyes: What the hell are you cooking up over there?
Aosta: A lose-lose situation brings me no benefit; that's all.
Aosta: The longer the experiment stays active, the more benefit it brings to my future research.
Kittyeyes: You want me to believe that you're just gonna give up like that?
Aosta: Roger's issue is one-of-a-kind; there exists no other being that can help him besides myself. One day, you will bring him to me yourself, I guarantee it.
Aosta: On a side note, there's a more desperate matter for you to tend to right now.
Roger: Jeff, are you really not coming with us?
Jeff: I have my own plans. Plus, I'm useless in a fight. If we run into danger, I'm nothing but a burden to you guys.
Roger: Is that so...alright then. Thank you for taking care of my sister and me throughout all these years.
Jeff: ... Kittyeyes, take good care of your brother. Someday, he will recover, and Koll will come back as well...
Kittyeyes: Thank you, Jeff. Goodbye.
Roger: Well...Kittyeyes, you mentioned a location where we could live in seclusion; where is it?
Kittyeyes: It's that way, takes about five days. Let's hit the road, brother!
Roger: Yes, let's go.
